The paper discusses the use of combinatorial double auctions for the assignment and pricing of shared rides in transportation network companies. This involves the optimization of social welfare and the allocation of resources based on customer and driver valuations. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.GT (Game Theory and Decision Science). The paper also proposes a new algorithm for this purpose, which involves optimization and heuristics, indicating that it could fall under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). The use of optimization and heuristics also suggests that the paper could be relevant to cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
